17:56.160 --> 17:58.380
This is Daryl Lane. And David Carson.

17:59.040 --> 18:01.660
He's one of the best-selling authors in the field of science fiction.

18:01.660 --> 18:04.960
A fairly large portion of his work falls into the Known Space series,

18:05.400 --> 18:08.000
a group of stories and novels with a consistent chronology.

18:08.540 --> 18:12.600
Such a series is called a Future History. Niven believes there are some peculiar

18:12.600 --> 18:15.300
attractions a Future History has for a science fiction author.

18:16.040 --> 18:22.600
There had been Future Histories around, Poul Anderson and Robert Heinlein.

18:24.540 --> 18:30.760
And I tell you, I guess we each evolved the idea somewhat independently.

18:31.200 --> 18:36.420
And the idea is that if you carved out a consistent workable future,

18:37.060 --> 18:39.800
it seems a shame to waste it on one story.

18:41.120 --> 18:47.920
You put it in the background because you want the background of a story to seem

18:48.480 --> 18:51.900
bigger than it is. So there are things that are simply unexplained.

18:53.320 --> 18:58.260
And if you think of more to say on a given subject, why you go with it?

18:58.440 --> 19:02.660
And if you think of a story that fits into the background of a previous story,

19:02.700 --> 19:04.860
it allows you to elaborate on that background.

19:05.440 --> 19:07.500
You sometimes you fall in love with the background.

19:08.060 --> 19:10.600
And presently you've got a bunch of stories that link.

19:22.240 --> 19:26.160
Niven has also written some bestselling books that fall outside his known space series.

19:26.660 --> 19:29.740
Three of these, The Mote in God's Eye, Lucifer's Hammer,

19:30.200 --> 19:33.140
and Oath of Fielty were written in collaboration with Jerry Pournelle.

19:33.620 --> 19:35.620
We asked Niven how he and Pournelle collaborate.

19:36.740 --> 19:45.000
Hard sometimes, but it always resolves. The question is who is most qualified to write a

19:45.520 --> 19:51.440
that we have both decided needs writing. Before we start, we have the novel all laid out.

19:52.400 --> 19:57.640
We know what's going in virtually everywhere. And if we don't, it feels like we do.

19:58.620 --> 20:02.100
And if we find out we don't, we elaborate as we get to that section.

20:03.500 --> 20:08.160
Okay, the next question is who is qualified to write a given scene? Sometimes it's obvious.

20:09.060 --> 20:11.400
If we're dealing with a mad man, he's mine.

20:12.040 --> 20:15.780
If we're dealing with military operations, it's Jerry's.

20:15.860 --> 20:24.920
Aliens are generally mine. Politics is generally Jerry's. Knowledge of history, generally Jerry's.

20:25.300 --> 20:32.520
And a real evil son of a bitch, Jerry usually creates him. And I usually run with him afterwards.

20:41.660 --> 20:46.460
Niven occasionally writes science fiction humor, or rarity. He talks about his most successful

20:46.460 --> 20:55.840
piece of humor. I suppose I could name old man of steel woman of queen eggs, which has gotten me

20:55.840 --> 21:01.900
the most laughs. I suppose everybody seems to have read it. Those who haven't have heard about it

21:01.900 --> 21:07.900
in a cocktail party. Niven's ready eye for humor can also be appreciated as he reveals that he's

21:07.900 --> 21:13.040
detected one of his own alien creations from Ringworld, a Pearson's Puppeteer here on Earth.

21:13.980 --> 21:17.180
I have reason to suspect a pair of puppeteers on Earth.

21:18.400 --> 21:24.240
Look at the characteristics. Forget the shape. They must be masters of biology that hide that

21:24.240 --> 21:29.900
peculiar three-legged two-headed shape. But consider their characteristics. They are cowards.

21:31.480 --> 21:37.440
That is, they want everything utterly safe. No corners on anything. Everything is soft,

21:37.440 --> 21:42.920
surfaces around the Puppeteer world. They don't even keep their world near a sun,

21:43.380 --> 21:52.100
regarding it as a runaway fusion reactor, which of course it is. So, desperate regard for safety,

21:52.280 --> 22:02.100
they plus an urge to meddle in the lifestyles of other species. Driving urge to meddle with

22:03.260 --> 22:08.180
practically no restraints attached. What does that remind you of? It seems nearly

22:08.180 --> 22:11.000
certain to me that Ralph Nader is a Pearson's puppeteer.

